"short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 121}, "passed": true}}, "text": "3. CHINA AND EAST EUROPEAN SATELLITES PUT ECONOMIC PRESSURE ON JAPAN\n\nthe European Satellites are co-operating with Communist China to exercise economic pressure on the Japanese.\n\nJapan is currently running an unfavorable balance of trade with China exceeding $50,000,000. East European Satellites have agreed not to pay for imports from Japan with foreign exchange which Japan could use to reduce its debt to China.\n\nBy this strategy and the refusal to accept additional commodities which Japan has offered to China, Peiping is attempting to prevent Japan from paying its debt. Peiping probably hopes to use Japan's increasing indebtedness to force it to establish official economic relations with Communist China, a first step toward diplomatic recognition.\n(Prepared jointly with ORR", "token_count": 121, "token_end_0based": 120, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "3 china and east european satellites put economic pressure on japan the european satellites are co-operating with communist china to exercise economic pressure on the japanese japan is currently running an unfavorable balance of trade with china exceeding 50 000 000 east european satellites have agreed not to pay for imports from japan with foreign exchange which japan could use to reduce its debt to china by this strategy and the refusal to accept additional commodities which japan has offered to china peiping is attempting to prevent japan from paying its debt peiping probably hopes to use japan's increasing indebtedness to force it to establish official economic relations with communist china a first step toward diplomatic recognition prepared jointly with orr", "unred_source_page": 7}
